      "text": [
        " \"فَلْيَقُمْ فِي اَلْمِعْبَرِ حَتَّى يَجُوزَهُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4316 - Al-Sakuni narrated from Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) from his father, Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), that Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib (as) was asked about a man who vowed to walk to the House of Allah (swt) but encountered a river crossing along the way. Imam (as) said: \"Let him stand in the crossing until he passes it.\""
        ]
      }
    },
